I think the accepted answer should be Eren Ersnmez&#x27;s.<p>Comparing<p><pre><code>        if (i > 0)
        {
            value += 2;
        }
        else
        {
            value += 3;
        }
</code></pre>
Is not the same as<p><pre><code>    value += i > 0 ? 2 : 3;
</code></pre>
Quoting the answer:<p><pre><code>    In one case, you create two different += operations with constant values and which one you 
    pick depends on a condition, and in the other case, you create a += where the value to add 
    depends on a condition.</code></pre>
